<s id="lets-play-strip-DandD" title="Let’s Play">

[

Emma Watson is sitting on a chair, in the field north of
<a href="https://www.shlomifish.org/philosophy/culture/multiverse-cosmology/#ramatavivgimel">Ramat Aviv Gimel</a>, Shlomi Fish’s home neighbourhood.

]

Emma Watson: good morning, good people. Today, three players and I are going
to try playing a striptease version of the tabletop role-playing game
<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dungeons_%26_Dragons">Dungeons &amp;
Dragons</a>. D&amp;D is a popular derivative of <a href="https://www.shlomifish.org/philosophy/culture/multiverse-cosmology/#fantasia-vs-fantastecha">the role-playing game of Greater Fantasia</a>

</s>

<s id="de-accessorising" title="De-accessorising">

Mr. T: well, Monsieur Titanium … God, all these gold/etc. accessories
sure accumulate heat.

Shlomi Fish: aren't they props?

Mr. T: they are, but they still got really warm.

Shlomi Fish: well, it is a hot day in the Israeli spring/summer (a “chamsin” ?).

Tiffany Alvord: to be honest, my accessories have accumulated a lot of heat too.

Emma Watson: same here!

Shlomi Fish: then let me summon my de-accessorising buddies from the Mossad. [Uses his smartphone] Hey, Fluttershy! Please send a Mossad de-accessorising unit to my GPS coordinates. [ References: <a href="https://shlomifishswiki.branchable.com/Fluttershy__44___Princess_of_Princesses__44___head_of_the_secret_cabal_leadership_of_the_Mossad__44___the_already_top_secret_intelligence_agency_of_the_Zionist_conspiracy/">“Fluttershy, Princess of Princesses, head of the secret cabal leadership of the Mossad, the already top secret intelligence agency of the Zionist conspiracy”</a>. ]

</s>

<s id="jojos-perspective" title="Jojo’s Perspective">

[

<b>Note:</b> a lot of the text here is hard-to-translate from the original Hebrew.

<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ha-Comedy_Store">Jojo from Ha-Comedy Store</a> is sitting behind his desk, wearing an elegant, non-leopardy, suit.

]

Jojo: אכן, מיליות כדורבנים. [ = “Indeed, wordlets like porcupines.” ]

Jojo: ועל כך אמרו חכמינו חז"ל לברכה: “אם יש לכם קשרים, אינכם צריכים פרוטקציה.”.
[ = “And <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chazal">our sages, Chazal,</a> said of that: ‘if you have contacts, you do not need protection’” ]

Jojo: ערב צח, ערב זך, ותודה שצפיתם בחלסטרה של ז'וז'ו. ותחשבו על זה![ = “have a pleasant evening, and thanks for watching ‘Jojo’s Tick-off’. And think about all that!” ]

[

The room turns dark for a few seconds, and then Jojo is seen wearing
only a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Undershirt">vest</a>, with a large picture of <a href="https://kungfupanda.fandom.com/wiki/Tigress">Tigress (from <i>Kung Fu Panda</i>)</a>.

Jojo glances at the view of the camera on his smartphone. He gets angry.

]

Jojo: מה זה החרטה הזה?! [ = “What the hell is this shit?!” ]

</s>

<s id="mr-linea-s-perspective" title="Mr. Linea’s Perspective">

[

Mr. Linea (from <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/La_Linea_(TV_series)">the <i>La Linea</i> television series</a>) is wearing a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trench_coat">Humphrey Bogart-like trench coat</a>, a hat. He is watching television.

]

Mr. Linea: hah, hah, hah, hah, hah… strip dee and dee en Jojo chalastrah

[

Mr. Linea gets hit by a lightning, which evaporates his clothes.

He looks down, and gasps startled. He runs leftward for several seconds
followed by the camera-like frame.

The camera stays in place, and Mr. Linea runs-out-of-frame, for a few seconds.
Then there are noises of entering the house, and dressing.

Mr. Linea enters the frame again - from the left while running rightward. He
is angry, and stops running, and complains to the story arbiters.

]

